WEBVTT

01:51.820 --> 01:54.489
[CROWD CHEERING IN DAMON'S HEAD]

02:34.404 --> 02:36.405
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

02:39.159 --> 02:41.077
Oh, jeez.

02:46.875 --> 02:48.251
Ugh.

02:48.418 --> 02:50.711
What? I'm sleeping, Ray.

02:50.921 --> 02:52.547
I need to talk to you. Buzz me in.

02:52.714 --> 02:54.090
I'm naked.

02:54.258 --> 02:56.133
I already seen you naked. Come on.

02:57.511 --> 02:59.303
Well, I've got company.

03:04.935 --> 03:06.102
Come on, Ray!

03:06.311 --> 03:08.396
It's the ass crack of dawn.
I'm not a Marine.

03:08.564 --> 03:10.982
- Talk from there.
- I don't wanna talk from here.

03:11.149 --> 03:13.609
- I can't even see you.
- Well, I can see you.

03:13.902 --> 03:17.321
So if you've got something to say, say it.
I'm all ears.

03:19.241 --> 03:21.492
Fine. Stay away from my wife.

03:21.994 --> 03:23.327
You don't have a wife.

03:23.495 --> 03:25.830
You know what I'm
talking about, Lenore.

03:25.998 --> 03:28.207
Oh, you mean your ex-wife, Jessica?

03:28.375 --> 03:30.209
The married woman
you secretly go bowling with?

03:30.377 --> 03:32.545
Yeah, her. Stay away from her, okay?

03:32.754 --> 03:34.505
Are you giving me an ultimatum, Ray?

03:34.756 --> 03:36.173
I'm Jessica's friend.

03:36.341 --> 03:39.844
I'm trying to save her from becoming
a sad two-time divorcÃ©e.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.387
What about you, Ray?

03:41.555 --> 03:45.391
What are you thinking about when you're
hugging her in a bowling alley parking lot?

03:45.559 --> 03:47.810
Are you thinking about
saving her marriage too...

03:47.978 --> 03:49.687
...or are you trying to destroy it?

03:50.731 --> 03:52.607
By the way, I have a new client for you.

03:52.816 --> 03:54.025
Tomorrow night, Tuesday.

03:54.192 --> 03:57.653
Will you be free, or will you be too busy
bowling with your ex-wife?

04:03.869 --> 04:05.870
When I say something, you say it back.

04:06.038 --> 04:08.748
So I say, uh, "You can't fuck me," right?

04:08.916 --> 04:11.667
So then you say...
Uh, repeat it back to me.

04:11.835 --> 04:15.630
Like, "You can't fuck me
because, uh, I don't want you to."

04:15.839 --> 04:19.675
[IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE] Tell her we need
the rent or we will kick her out on the street.

04:19.843 --> 04:22.261
You owe us two months' rent.
Do you think you might have it soon?

04:22.429 --> 04:23.596
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

04:23.764 --> 04:25.765
Hold on, I just... Hold that thought.

04:25.933 --> 04:27.558
I don't know who this is.

04:27.893 --> 04:30.019
Why haven't you picked up your phone?
We need to talk.

04:30.187 --> 04:31.687
- Uh, Ray...
- Hi.

04:31.855 --> 04:34.357
Ray, this is, um, Mr. And Mrs. Sumbal.

04:34.524 --> 04:38.235
They're my very kind, generous
and very patient landlords.

04:38.403 --> 04:41.822
Listen, Tanya,
I have a problem with Lenore.

04:41.990 --> 04:44.283
- What? What kind of problem?
- Well, I, uh...

04:44.451 --> 04:45.910
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

04:46.078 --> 04:48.454
You know, I have
a very bad feeling about her.

04:48.622 --> 04:51.749
You know, she has a lot
of our personal information...

04:51.917 --> 04:53.167
...and I don't trust her.

04:53.335 --> 04:55.544
You know, I... To tell you the truth...

04:55.754 --> 04:58.089
...I don't like the way she treats you.

04:58.256 --> 04:59.924
Uh, would you like some olives?

05:00.509 --> 05:03.135
[IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE] If I don't get rent,
I will throw your teapots out on the sidewalk.

05:03.303 --> 05:05.513
My husband says we might have to charge
a $50 late fee.

05:05.722 --> 05:07.890
The thing is, I don't have it.
I don't have it.

05:08.058 --> 05:09.308
I'm $300 short, you know?

05:09.476 --> 05:12.019
What do you want from me?
I've lived here 15 years.

05:12.187 --> 05:13.771
Remember the rat in the dryer?

05:13.939 --> 05:15.731
Did I complain? I didn't. I'm not now.

05:15.899 --> 05:17.608
I just... We have a good relationship.

05:17.776 --> 05:19.568
I need to talk to my friend. Hold on.

05:19.736 --> 05:21.904
Maybe you're right.
Maybe we're better off without her.

05:22.072 --> 05:24.240
Uh. Okay, why are you saying this?

05:24.408 --> 05:25.658
Did something happen?

05:25.909 --> 05:27.535
- No.
- No? All right, well then...

05:27.703 --> 05:29.036
Ray, I just... You know what?

05:29.246 --> 05:30.287
I just don't think...

05:30.455 --> 05:32.039
...you're being very professional.
- Huh?

05:32.207 --> 05:36.127
You can't just have a bad feeling and
let go of our business partner right now.

05:37.087 --> 05:40.339
- Why not?
- Because it all comes down to the clients.

05:40.799 --> 05:42.800
All right?
That's the clients and the money.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.802
If I can't come up with the clients...

05:44.970 --> 05:47.805
...you'll run back to Lenore
when she shows up with new ones.

05:47.973 --> 05:49.807
- You know that.
- That's what I'm asking.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.184
Can you get them without her?

05:52.686 --> 05:55.062
Yes, Ray. Yes. Okay?

05:55.230 --> 05:58.315
I will book that wealthy widow
Frances, Ray.

05:58.525 --> 06:03.195
I think of her like Moby-Dick,
and I'm Ahab, except successful.

06:05.949 --> 06:07.324
You've read Moby-Dick, right?

06:08.326 --> 06:09.493
Mm-hm.

06:13.582 --> 06:16.042
Oh. Hi.

06:16.209 --> 06:17.918
Want me to scrub you?

06:18.086 --> 06:20.087
Thanks, honey. I'm clean.

06:23.592 --> 06:26.218
- You okay, Ron?
- Yeah, I'm better than okay.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.804
I'm hopeful and I love you...

06:28.972 --> 06:30.890
...and I've been thinking about our talk.

06:31.058 --> 06:34.643
- Which talk?
- About the baby. No pressure.

06:34.811 --> 06:37.438
We don't have to talk
about that right now.

06:37.606 --> 06:40.858
I was just thinking of my family.

06:41.526 --> 06:45.821
- You mean you and me and the kids?
- Yeah.

06:45.989 --> 06:49.950
And the ones who came before us,
like my grandfather.

06:50.118 --> 06:53.329
People said he had the perfect nose.

06:53.789 --> 06:55.331
Are you sure you're okay, Ron?

06:55.499 --> 06:58.250
There's no face problems
in my family, Jess.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.961
No Alzheimer's, no celiac disease...

07:01.129 --> 07:03.339
...no Klinefelter's syndrome,
no Tay-Sachs...

07:03.507 --> 07:07.218
- Ron, you're talking about the baby again.
- Yes.

07:07.552 --> 07:11.764
Jess, I'm talking about the baby again
because I want a baby.

07:12.265 --> 07:13.891
I want to pass on that tradition.

07:14.601 --> 07:17.186
I am 42 years old, Ron.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.688
I'm not having a baby with you.

07:26.321 --> 07:28.656
RONNIE: I went to medical school.
I am not a drug addict.

07:29.199 --> 07:30.908
I've never been incarcerated.

07:31.076 --> 07:33.702
I am a good man from a good family...

07:33.870 --> 07:36.956
...in a good neighborhood
and I'm hungry!

07:37.124 --> 07:40.459
I am in my kitchen,
searching for my oatmeal...

07:40.627 --> 07:43.087
...that I purchased
with the money I made...

07:43.255 --> 07:47.633
...with the job I still have
in this crumbling fucking economy...

07:47.801 --> 07:50.261
...because I want breakfast!

07:50.428 --> 07:52.263
I want that fucking oatmeal!

07:52.430 --> 07:55.599
I want my cinnamon fucking oatmeal!

07:56.977 --> 07:58.936
This is not what I signed up for!

07:59.104 --> 08:02.356
This is not the life of my dreams!

08:15.036 --> 08:17.079
Mr. Landy told you this?

08:18.165 --> 08:20.207
Mr. Landy the security guard?

08:21.793 --> 08:23.544
I'm sorry, Ray.

08:24.754 --> 08:26.463
He said it was Damon?

08:26.631 --> 08:30.092
It was him, Ray, your son...

08:30.385 --> 08:32.261
...taking a leak on home plate.

08:35.974 --> 08:38.100
[SIGHS]

08:38.268 --> 08:39.810
RAY:
He pissed on home plate, Tanya.

08:40.061 --> 08:41.312
- Two in the morning.
- Yeah.

08:41.479 --> 08:42.771
All alone.

08:42.939 --> 08:48.027
He waltzed down to the diamond,
unzipped his fly and just let loose.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.613
I think I can see what he was going for.

08:50.780 --> 08:53.407
- You can see what he was going for?
- Come on, Ray.

08:53.575 --> 08:56.660
You know, the plate of home?
A place called home?

08:56.828 --> 08:59.246
He was releasing his anger
in a nonviolent way.

08:59.414 --> 09:01.916
He was releasing, all right.
I don't know about anger.

09:02.083 --> 09:03.918
I'm just saying, he might be an artist.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.794
He didn't paint, Tanya. He peed.

09:06.129 --> 09:07.963
All right,
maybe he needs a role model.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.341
Yeah, that would be me.
You know, I'm his dad.

09:10.508 --> 09:13.010
Fine, but maybe he needs
someone else to look up to...

09:13.178 --> 09:14.970
...like a fellow traveler, you know?

09:15.138 --> 09:16.847
Someone who shares his interests.

09:17.015 --> 09:18.682
Wait, I got an idea.

09:18.850 --> 09:22.436
Here, just... Just bring him to this.

09:24.648 --> 09:26.607
"Slam Bam Poetry Slam."

09:26.775 --> 09:29.276
"Sam..." "Slam Bam Poetry Jam."

09:29.444 --> 09:30.653
No, thanks.

09:30.820 --> 09:33.530
Ray, you can't just throw stuff
off the skywalk.

09:33.698 --> 09:35.824
I can get it. Wait, hold on.

09:36.409 --> 09:38.118
See, it's right...

09:39.663 --> 09:41.121
Oh, God.

09:41.873 --> 09:43.582
What are you doing?
Are you all right?

09:43.750 --> 09:45.251
Yeah, I'm fine, Ray.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.044
- What happened?
- It's just stupid.

09:47.212 --> 09:49.296
Come on, let's go. I'm fine.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.800
You know, Ray,
I'm making a serious suggestion.

09:52.968 --> 09:55.427
I think poetry might
really speak to Damon.

09:55.679 --> 09:57.763
Great, maybe my son's a good rhymer.

09:57.931 --> 10:00.099
No offense, but I don't think
beret-wearing strangers...

10:00.267 --> 10:01.642
...is what my kid needs right now.

10:01.810 --> 10:04.144
Okay, shh. There she is.

10:04.312 --> 10:06.981
- Where?
- Uh, two o'clock.

10:07.148 --> 10:10.442
She's eating a chicken bowl
in an $800 shirt.

10:10.652 --> 10:12.444
Don't look at her though.
Look at me.

10:12.612 --> 10:15.072
- What? Why?
- Because...

10:15.532 --> 10:17.908
...she wants to look at you.

10:19.202 --> 10:20.953
- She does?
- Yeah.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.038
Well, what...? What, uh...?

10:23.206 --> 10:24.331
- I thought... Heh.
- What?

10:24.499 --> 10:26.458
- I thought I was supposed to meet her.
- No.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.460
She likes to do things
a step at a time.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.755
So this time she'll just
take a look from afar. Ahem.

10:31.923 --> 10:33.340
All right.

10:33.508 --> 10:35.676
I don't know what she can tell
from over there.

10:35.844 --> 10:39.388
That you're reasonably good-Iooking
and not dangerous.

10:40.098 --> 10:41.432
Okay, that's it.

10:41.599 --> 10:42.933
- That's it?
- That's it.

10:43.393 --> 10:45.019
I came all this way just for that?

10:45.228 --> 10:48.272
This is Moby-Dick, Ray.
Trust me, she's worth it.

10:59.242 --> 11:00.576
I'm sorry.

11:00.785 --> 11:03.078
You really need oatmeal that bad?

11:03.246 --> 11:04.538
Mother.

11:19.846 --> 11:21.388
Jess...

11:22.307 --> 11:25.309
...I've loved you
since the 10th grade...

11:25.977 --> 11:29.521
...since that math class
you ignored me in...

11:30.398 --> 11:33.108
...since before you even knew
I was alive.

11:34.486 --> 11:37.196
I told you I didn't wanna have babies
because I was scared.

11:37.364 --> 11:40.366
I was afraid you wouldn't marry me
if I told you the truth...

11:42.452 --> 11:45.120
...but I wanna be on the inside, Jess.

11:47.791 --> 11:51.210
I love you more than life itself.

11:51.378 --> 11:53.420
I love you too, Ron.

11:55.256 --> 11:57.549
I want you to be on the inside too.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.427
Thank you.

12:01.596 --> 12:04.139
Today's the happiest day
of my life.

12:05.100 --> 12:07.267
I'm gonna be a father.

12:23.451 --> 12:25.035
Anything you wanna tell me?

12:25.245 --> 12:27.538
- Like what?
- I don't know.

12:27.914 --> 12:32.418
But if there is anything you wanna say,
you can tell me.

12:32.585 --> 12:34.628
I'm your dad. I love you.

12:36.423 --> 12:40.717
You know, my dad,
he had this, uh, extra business...

12:41.386 --> 12:43.971
...making decoys. Ducks.

12:44.180 --> 12:47.641
Mallards, redheads, you named it,
he carved it. He loved it.

12:48.393 --> 12:50.269
Every second he got...

12:50.478 --> 12:54.148
...he was back there in that tool shed
with his little decoy ducks.

12:55.859 --> 12:58.277
But really I wanted to crush
those ducks, you know?

12:58.445 --> 13:00.320
I wanted to snap their little heads off.

13:03.450 --> 13:07.536
Mr. Landy saw you, son.
The other night, he saw you.

13:07.787 --> 13:10.998
You urinated on America's pastime, son.

13:11.166 --> 13:13.292
I didn't get you in trouble, did I?

13:14.043 --> 13:15.335
No.

13:15.503 --> 13:18.589
No, but what I'm saying is we're alike.

13:19.132 --> 13:20.591
I can understand you.

13:20.758 --> 13:22.676
We're... We're...

13:22.844 --> 13:27.514
You know, we're fellow, uh, travelers.

13:28.349 --> 13:30.934
It's normal to wanna
get back at your old man.

13:31.144 --> 13:34.021
It's okay if it was me
you wanted to piss on.

13:34.772 --> 13:36.899
I didn't wanna piss on you, Dad.

13:37.066 --> 13:39.151
I just drank a lot of pop.

13:59.422 --> 14:02.674
Hi. I'm, uh, checking in.

14:03.426 --> 14:06.261
- I'm picking up a key.
WOMAN: May I have your name, please?

14:06.429 --> 14:10.641
It's... It's mister... Mr. Falls.

14:10.808 --> 14:11.850
I'm Mr. Falls.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.770
Ray? Ray!

14:14.938 --> 14:16.480
- Mike.
- Buddy!

14:16.648 --> 14:20.692
Oh, man, it's good to see
a friendly face, pal.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.153
Being single's hard enough,
but single alone...

14:23.321 --> 14:25.322
I haven't said two words
since I got here.

14:25.698 --> 14:27.491
What are you drinking? I'm buying.

14:27.700 --> 14:30.202
No. No, thanks, Mike. I...

14:30.537 --> 14:32.871
Damn, you're getting a room already?

14:33.039 --> 14:34.373
Uh-huh.

14:34.541 --> 14:35.749
Optimistic, huh?

14:35.917 --> 14:37.334
- Here, Mr. Falls.
- Thank you.

14:37.544 --> 14:40.212
- Fifteenth floor. Enjoy your stay.
- Falls? Who's that?

14:40.380 --> 14:42.589
Beats me. I'm not here
for the singles thing, Mike.

14:42.757 --> 14:44.675
Oh. Ohh. What are you here for?

14:44.842 --> 14:47.302
Um, a different thing.

14:47.804 --> 14:48.845
- In a hotel room?
- Yeah.

14:49.013 --> 14:50.931
Hey, great to see you, pal.

14:51.099 --> 14:52.975
You look, uh... You look good.

14:53.142 --> 14:54.726
- Yeah.
- Go knock them dead.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.311
Yeah.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.188
You too.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.568
- Hello?
WOMAN: Come in.

15:17.709 --> 15:19.126
Wow.

15:26.217 --> 15:27.801
- Hi.
- Hi.

15:28.052 --> 15:30.929
- Cake?
- No, thanks. Heh.

15:32.015 --> 15:33.098
Wow.

15:41.566 --> 15:42.691
You're cute.

15:54.162 --> 15:55.412
[GIGGLES]

15:55.580 --> 15:57.664
You wanna do it on the floor?

15:57.832 --> 15:58.874
Sure.

16:03.546 --> 16:05.297
[MOANS]

16:06.257 --> 16:07.924
My turn.

16:10.219 --> 16:11.803
[LAUGHS]

16:12.472 --> 16:14.473
[MOANING]

16:21.689 --> 16:23.190
Go for it.

16:28.655 --> 16:30.280
I'm Christina.

16:30.448 --> 16:31.865
Richard.

16:32.450 --> 16:34.034
- Today's my birthday.
- Oh, yeah?

16:34.494 --> 16:36.578
- Happy birthday.
- Thanks.

16:36.746 --> 16:38.538
You're my birthday present.

16:38.873 --> 16:40.582
Hey! Oh, yes.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.459
Sing for me, will you?

16:42.960 --> 16:44.461
What would you like to hear?

16:44.629 --> 16:48.715
It's my birthday.
Sing "Happy Birthday." Ha, ha.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.385
Um, uh...

16:51.552 --> 16:56.390
[RAY SINGING]

16:57.392 --> 16:58.433
Oh, yeah.

17:01.938 --> 17:04.064
Yeah. Ugh. Oh!

17:07.902 --> 17:10.153
Oh, perfect, yeah. Unh.

17:15.785 --> 17:17.911
[MOANING]

17:18.496 --> 17:20.872
- Wow.
- Ha-ha-ha.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.499
- Sing it again, okay?
- Um...

17:22.667 --> 17:23.959
One more time.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.128
[SINGING]

17:26.295 --> 17:28.338
- Wait, wait, wait. Start from the top.
- Okay.

17:28.506 --> 17:30.632
- I love it. Unh.
- Okay.

17:32.593 --> 17:34.886
Ha! Unh!

17:35.054 --> 17:36.972
Again.

17:37.140 --> 17:39.307
Loud.

17:39.475 --> 17:40.559
Soft.

17:40.768 --> 17:42.769
- Sing it again.
- Again?

17:42.937 --> 17:45.856
Slow.

17:46.023 --> 17:48.400
With an accent. Irish.

17:51.154 --> 17:52.946
- I can't do an accent.
- No?

17:53.114 --> 17:55.240
Softer then.

17:55.408 --> 17:57.367
No, loud. I'm sorry, loud.

17:57.535 --> 18:00.871
[RAY SINGING LOUDLY]

18:01.038 --> 18:02.080
Don't stop. Keep it up.

18:03.541 --> 18:04.583
Sing it again.

18:10.798 --> 18:12.758
I feel so badly about what happened.

18:12.967 --> 18:15.761
If it's any consolation,
I had the agency fire that guy.

18:15.970 --> 18:17.763
We don't need to talk about that.

18:17.930 --> 18:20.974
That whole sex therapist thing,
that is not who I am.

18:21.142 --> 18:22.559
I know.

18:23.102 --> 18:24.895
- But if you wanna try again...
- I don't.

18:25.062 --> 18:28.148
- I promise, the guy will not stand you up.
- I don't.

18:31.819 --> 18:32.944
God, look at him. Ha, ha.

18:33.613 --> 18:35.697
He said yesterday was
the happiest day of his life.

18:35.865 --> 18:38.950
Ha-ha-ha. Maybe it was.

18:39.452 --> 18:41.119
But I didn't say yes, Lenore.

18:41.329 --> 18:43.205
I just told him that I loved him.

18:43.372 --> 18:44.998
I mean, what was I supposed to say?

18:45.166 --> 18:47.334
He says he's been
in love with me since...

18:47.502 --> 18:49.377
...before I was alive.

18:50.797 --> 18:53.215
Well, you could be clear
your answer is no.

18:53.382 --> 18:54.674
Mm.

18:54.842 --> 18:58.136
- There's also the option of saying yes.
- What?

18:58.346 --> 19:01.348
I'm trying to save your marriage
any way I can, Jess.

19:01.516 --> 19:04.601
I'm worried.
I mean, bowling with your ex-husband?

19:04.769 --> 19:07.270
- What was that the other night?
- Wha...? Nothing.

19:07.730 --> 19:09.773
- That doesn't mean anything.
- Ha, ha.

19:10.608 --> 19:12.067
So is he single?

19:13.945 --> 19:15.987
I assume so. Why?

19:16.155 --> 19:19.950
I know a lot of ladies that would
really appreciate someone like him.

19:23.746 --> 19:27.082
But not as much as they would appreciate
what you have here with Ronnie.

19:27.333 --> 19:29.376
Hello? Look at this place.
It's gorgeous.

19:29.961 --> 19:33.505
You have a house big enough for you,
your mom, your kids.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.423
You have a man who loves you...

19:35.591 --> 19:38.051
...who lives in it with you.

